sentences.english: Anna was born in 1923 in Ardwick, a suburb of Manchester.
sentences.chinese: 安娜于1923年出生在曼彻斯特的郊区阿德维克。

sentences.english: This initiative helped improve registration of births and deaths at the subdistrict level.
sentences.chinese: 这一举措帮助改善了街道一级的出生和死亡登记。

sentences.english: She has been doctoring since before you were born.
sentences.chinese: 从你们出生前至今，她一直在行医。

sentences.english: The less girl were inconsolable at the loss of IT kitten.
sentences.chinese: 那个小女刚出生的孩子因失去她的小猫而伤心不已。

sentences.english: Adeline Yen Mah was born in Tianjin, China.
sentences.chinese: 严君玲在中国天津出生。

sentences.english: The prevalence rates increased with increasing gravidity or parity.
sentences.chinese: 出生缺陷发生率随着孕产次的增加而明显提高。

sentences.english: I was born on August the third of nineteen ninety-nine.
sentences.chinese: 我在一九九九年八月三号出生。

sentences.english: Mr. Rolston was born in the state of Virginia in 1932.
sentences.chinese: 罗尔斯顿先生1932年出生在弗吉尼亚。

sentences.english: In which country was Ibrahim Afellay born?
sentences.chinese: 阿费莱出生在哪个国家？

sentences.english: Male circumcision is common at birth in the United States.
sentences.chinese: 男婴出生时行包皮环切术在美国很普遍。

sentences.english: Ultimately, of course, the birth-order debate will never be entirely settled.
sentences.chinese: 最后，当然对于出生顺序的争论将永远不会完全平息。

sentences.english: My cousin was born in China and grew up in Australia.
sentences.chinese: 我的表妹出生在中国，在澳大利亚长大。

sentences.english: I was born in the village of Minquan, in Henan province.
sentences.chinese: 在河南郑州的民权村出生。

sentences.english: Deer can run from the time they are born until they die.
sentences.chinese: 鹿子从出生到死亡都可能奔跑。

sentences.english: Gray was born in Canton, Ohio.
sentences.chinese: 格雷出生在俄亥俄的坎顿。
